The paper deals with the problem of answering marginal queries on a database while preserving differential privacy, which is a fundamental problem in private data analysis. This problem is closely related to data structures (cs.DS), cryptography (cs.CR), information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper proposes a new algorithm for answering marginal queries that is based on a low-weight representation of the database, which is a technique commonly used in data structures and information theory. The paper also analyzes the accuracy of the algorithm, which is a topic of interest in machine learning and computational complexity.
